sub_title: DLR Clinical Aerospace Medicine Intern | MSS23 & SHSSP22 @ISU
summary:
I am interested in developing state-of-the-art solutions to humanize technology and to enable space travellers to tolerate off-world environments to explore deep space. 

I have a background in Industrial Design with specialization in Leadership and Entrepreneurship. My project work is ranging from designing a smart suit for Paralympic swimmers in the Netherlands to training local farmers in Senegal to soilless techniques to address food insecurity. 
Besides, I have international working records in social entrepreneurship and digital design in sectors such as healthcare, food security, construction and e-learning. 

I am currently finishing up the Master of Studies at the International Space University.
